  "text": "The Kafka ProduceRequest path is traced through five files, all within the kafka repo. (1) KafkaProducer.send() accepts a ProducerRecord and callback, serializes the key/value, and calls RecordAccumulator.append(). (2) RecordAccumulator.append() batches records into per-partition queues. (3) Sender.sendProducerData() (called from the Sender I/O thread's run loop) drains ready batches from the accumulator and builds ProduceRequests. (4) NetworkClient.send() enqueues the request for transmission over the network to a broker. (5) On the broker side, ReplicaManager.appendRecords() (Scala) handles the incoming ProduceRequest by appending records to the partition logs. Note that ReplicaManager is implemented in Scala, not Java, as is typical for Kafka's server-side code.",
